              If you get into homebrewing because you think you'll save money vs buying craft beer, you're getting into homebrewing for the wrong reasons.  You really don't save money over craft beer, but you DO get the satisfaction of knowing you're drinking a beer YOU made, making what you like, etc.. and at least I think brewing is enjoyable.  Plus, all the cool stuff you can do with your beers... <br /><br />That all being said I just opened one of my chocolate cherry stouts that I bottled ~2 weeks ago.  Last week the carbonation wasn't right, and there wasn't much head.  MUCH better now.<br /><br />Click for larger pic<br /><a href="http://imgur.com/4zfkpLB" class="postlink" rel="nofollow"><img src="http://i.imgur.com/4zfkpLBs.jpg" alt="Image" /></a>

              

              
              
