        <tr>
          <td class="post-content">
            <div class="post-content-inner">
              
              Does anyone have any wisdom to impart on thick vs thin mashes?  I do BIAB with a sort-of-sparge (bag in a colander perched over a bucket, I dump 1 gallon of room temp water over the bag and collect the runnings in the bucket.  I've had some batches with good efficiency, and some with bad efficiency, and looking at my notes, it does look like the closer I am to 2qts of water per lb of grain, the better my efficiency is.  <br /><br />I know 1.25qt/lb is supposed to be standard.  What sort of side-effects am I looking at for a thin mash?

              

              
              
            </div>
          </td>
        </tr>
        
    </table>
    
